<subSubSection lastPageId="476" lastPageNumber="477" pageId="475" pageNumber="476" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="475" pageNumber="476">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="476" lastPageNumber="477" pageId="475" pageNumber="476">
This species extends from Connecticut and &quot;Rhode Island&quot; (Sikes 2003: 8) to southern Minnesota and northeastern Nebraska, south to the Rio Grande in 
<pageBreakToken pageId="476" pageNumber="477" start="start">south-central</pageBreakToken>
New Mexico and southeastern Texas, and the Florida Keys [see Erwin 1970a: Fig. 201].
</paragraph>
